# ── Development ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Do NOT set VITE_API_URL in development.
# Vite proxies all /api requests to https://localhost:7089 automatically.
# This avoids CORS entirely — the browser sees one origin (localhost:3000).
#
# If your backend runs on the HTTP profile instead, change vite.config.ts:
#   target: 'http://localhost:5010'   (and remove secure: false)

# ── Production ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set this in your CI/CD pipeline or cloud host environment variables.
# It must be the full base URL of your deployed API (no trailing slash, no /api).
# The frontend appends /api paths automatically.
#
# Example:
# VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
#
# On Vercel: Project Settings → Environment Variables → VITE_API_URL
# On Netlify: Site settings → Build & deploy → Environment → VITE_API_URL
# On Azure Static Web Apps: Configuration → Application settings → VITE_API_URL
